[3] Australia (Townsville)
Date: 12 Apr 2007
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: ABC Radio [edited]
<http://www.abc.net.au/news/items/200704/1895477.htm?northqld>

Dengue fever cases rise to 17 in Townsville
-----------------------------------------------
Another person in the twin cities of Townsville and Thuringowa in
north Queensland has been confirmed to have dengue fever, taking the
number of cases 17.
The initial outbreak occurred in South Townsville at the end of last
month [March 2007].
The senior medical entomologist at Townsville's Tropical Population
Health Unit says work is continuing in the region to place mosquito
traps and remove potential breeding areas.
Gerhard Ehlers says he is expecting more cases to be confirmed before
the current outbreak is over.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[A map of Australia can be accessed at:
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/australia/australia_pol99.jpg>.
